> Though these may be Italian style meatballs, they're made with 100% Irish beef. Accompanied by a side of crispy roast potatoes and topped with melted mozzarella, this is a dish that everyone's sure to love.

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potatoes onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @Oil{to taste}, season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer (leaving room for the meatballs).

To a large #bowl{}, add the @Irish Beef Mince{250%grams}, @Breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @Mustard{1%sachet} and @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet}.

Season with salt and pepper then mix everything together with your hands.

Once combined, form into evenly-sized meatballs, 5 per person. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the oven is hot, cook the potatoes and beef meatballs together for ~{15%mins}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the @Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic{1%pack}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%ml} (double both for 4p). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-7%mins}.

Stir in the @Baby Spinach{60%grams} and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%mins}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir through a knob of @Butter{to taste}.

When the potatoes and meatballs have been cooking for 15 mins, remove the meatballs from the oven (leaving the potatoes to cook).

Add the meatballs to an #oven dish{}.

Stir in the simmered spinach sauce.

Drain then roughly tear the @Mozzarella{125%grams} and spread it on top.

Place the oven dish in the oven below the potatoes.

Bake everything until the mozzarella has melted and the potatoes are tender, ~{10-15%mins}. IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Divide the mozzarella meatballs between plates.

Serve with the crispy potatoes alongside.